    "body": "Since Spack has control over basically any dependency that can be build inside a user's `.local/`, setting the environment var [`PYTHONNOUSERSITE`](https://docs.python.org/2/using/cmdline.html#environment-variables) (or `PYTHONUSERBASE=/dev/null`) for python installs (and loads) (Python 2.6+ feature) could help to isolate our installs better from the outside world\u2122.\r\n\r\nAny concerns?\r\n\r\nccing @tgamblin @hartzell @junghans @alalazo @adamjstewart \r\n\r\nRelated (tricky) issues:\r\n- https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/issues/1229\r\n- https://github.com/spack/spack/issues/6558",
